title: For Sale:  Gewehr G43 AC 44 Walther
postcontent: This is an excellent example of an earlier/ mid-WWII German Army issue, Walther G43 semi-automatic sniper rifle with matching serial numbers excluding stock. This specific rifle has the earlier G43 markings that were used during the early part of 1944 production. These were the standard, mid/late war German sniper rifles intended to replace the K98 sniper rifles. It has A forged single bolt guide receiver that is marked on the left side "G43/ 142c/ac 44", with a single "eagle/359" Waffenamt proof on the right side. It is fitted with the rough forged bolt carrier that has the hold-open latch with the cocking handle on the left side. It has the stamped action cover with the sliding dust cover on top and a single Waffenamt proof on the rear end. The rifle is fitted with a correct wartime laminated stock ( different serial number) with a smooth cupped buttplate. The left side of stock has a partial "eagle/359" proof with a smaller one inside the pistol grip. This excellent G43 sniper rifle is complete with a correct WWII "aye/K43" marked magazine and leather strap but does not include cleaning rod.  The rifle was recently checked out at gunsmith and is range ready.  Slight pitting in rifling near end of muzzle which should not detriment accuracy.I prefer to meet at local Southern California FFL and do transfer.  However, I will ship to your FFL as an option.
